.TH "pkcs7_get_content_data" 9 "pkcs7_get_content_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pkcs7_get_content_data \- Get access to the PKCS#7 content
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pkcs7_get_content_data
.BI "(const struct pkcs7_message *pkcs7 "  ","
.BI "const void **_data "  ","
.BI "size_t *_data_len "  ","
.BI "size_t *_headerlen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pkcs7" 12
The preparsed PKCS#7 message to access
.IP "_data" 12
Place to return a pointer to the data
.IP "_data_len" 12
Place to return the data length
.IP "_headerlen" 12
Size of ASN.1 header not included in _data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Get access to the data content of the PKCS#7 message.  The size of the
header of the ASN.1 object that contains it is also provided and can be used
to adjust *_data and *_data_len to get the entire object.

Returns -ENODATA if the data object was missing from the message.
